modules.description: This module handles video frame manipulation through configuration and conversion operations, such as adjusting formats, quality, and scale modes, while managing pixel data arrays, rectangle coordinates, and transformation flags. It enables precise control over image processing tasks like resizing, cropping, and format adaptation. Use cases include optimizing video streams for different resolutions or encoding standards.

Provides functions for parsing and manipulating GAVL (Group, Artifact, Version, Classifier) strings, including splitting into components, reconstructing from parts, and comparing versions. Operates on strings and custom type representations of GAVL identifiers. Used to process Maven dependency specifications and version constraints in build systems.

Handles video frame manipulation with configuration and conversion operations, including format adjustment, quality control, and scale mode application. It manages pixel data arrays, rectangle coordinates, and transformation flags to enable precise image processing tasks such as resizing, cropping, and format adaptation. Operations include modifying frame dimensions, applying transformations, and converting between pixel formats. Examples include optimizing video streams for different resolutions or encoding standards by adjusting frame properties dynamically.
